Introduction: The young people who stay at home, through the interactive bullet screen communication, completed a not gathered, but the same lively and extraordinary "cloud music festival" experience, to resolve the feelings of emptiness and anxiety.

By U Thant

"It's snowing all the time today. Let all the old-fashioned emotions go away with time. " February 5, in Beijing's second snowfall since 2020, Peng Lei, the lead singer of the new pants band, stood downstairs with a guitar, playing "out of date" while the snow fell in the night sky. The original single, released on his personal weibo account, quickly garnered 2.75 million views.

By U Thant

"It's snowing all the time today. Let all the old-fashioned emotions go away with time. " February 5, in Beijing's second snowfall since 2020, Peng Lei, the lead singer of the new pants band, stood downstairs with a guitar, playing "out of date" while the snow fell in the night sky. The original single, released on his personal weibo account, quickly garnered 2.75 million views.

On this Special Spring Festival, Peng Lei stays at home for more than ten days, playing and singing for netizens every day, and each song gets hundreds of thousands of hits. New Pants has also posted a new single, "our shame to express our feelings 2020, " with the lyrics "long and boring vacation, empty city / charming freedom, trapped in a small mire. " That seems to fit the current scenario. Peng Lei wrote: "these two days to re-record and fill in the lyrics of this version, to represent the state of mind during this very period. ". We are lucky that literary and artistic people can read, watch movies, draw and listen to music in their idle time so that we are not bored."

When "Zhai" becomes the core word of this Spring Festival, independent musicians are not willing to idle away their time at home. In addition to new pants, bands such as hedgehog and penicillin have posted videos of their songs on Weibo, "singing at home, I hope everything will get better soon. "

Tongyang was the first band to donate $1 million on Jan. 24, a sizable donation that is certainly a large sum for an Indie rock band and is the sum of their income from dozens of shows. But Tongyang said, "Wuhan has always been the most blood-soaked city on our annual tour, and we just want to do our best, that's all. "

People are still living at home, watching the breathtaking statistics from the front line and reading the helpless, Sad, heart-wrenching, moving reports of the epidemic. At the moment, music brings not only relief, but also comfort and encouragement.

An unusual music festival

Wuhan Music Fan Xiaosuo has been a regular visitor to the strawberry festival for years. This time of year, Modern Sky would announce the lineup and information of the 2020 Wuhan Strawberry Festival, but an outbreak broke all the rhythm.

She keeps an eye on modern sky, but is surprised to find a free and special "curbside strawberry is not a music festival" .

The theme of "Hi, I'm home too" is like a cordial greeting. From Feb. 4 to 8, the six-hour live music broadcast, at 4 p.m. each day, brought zoot together with fans across the country. This is undoubtedly a new exploration and attempt in the performance industry.

For five days in a row, modern sky brought together 70 groups of musicians for a live webcast. There's live music from the musicians at home, as well as live video from the 2019 Strawberry Festival.

"everyone who looks good, enjoys it, and likes it has arrived, " said CEO  Yongqiang of Xiaofeng Performing Culture Industry Group, who counted musicians from Song Dongye, Xie Tianxiao and other festival regulars, there are also new pants, penicillin, Mr. Turtle and other positive hot band combination.

In addition to singing in the rehearsal room or living room with their guitars, they also display the most daily life. Song Dongye makes traditional spring cakes in the kitchen, and the family's adorable cat is on camera. Ding Wu wears a mask to hold a food class, and five drummers show how to make sour soup with pork belly. The musician Daxi teaches boys how to cut hair at home, full Shook releases new songs for the cameras, Zuo Zhai teaches fans to play the Acoustic Guitar version of the Golden Age at his home in Ningbo, and Cao Shi, the lead singer of the Band Black Caesar, demonstrates his gaming skills, a teacher teaches music fans to dance at home.

Young people at home, through interactive bomb screen communication, completed a do not need to gather, but the same lively extraordinary "cloud music festival" experience, to resolve the feelings of emptiness and anxiety. For days on end, while listening to music, Xiao Suo felt that he was not alone as he watched the heated discussion among music fans from all over the country.

The entire group was just three days from preparation to launch, according to Modern Sky's nerd berry working group. During the preparations, Modern Sky's offices in Beijing were closed, and the entire staff worked around the clock to complete the special festival. "curtilage strawberry" 5 days live during a total of more than 100 million views, the highest daily number of 490,000 online, the highest daily number of nearly 100,000 bullet screen.

This online music festival also gives modern sky more inspiration and space, in the advent of 5G, perhaps the music industry can usher in a new model and era.

On-line, off-line music relay

From Feb. 1 to March 1, the National Centre for the Performing Arts canceled nearly 30 shows.

From the moment the cancellation was announced, the National Centre for the Performing Arts launched a daily live online show. Including the Opera Aida, more than 1,000 live high definition performances, more than 2,700 Chinese and foreign music records, more than 4,000 behind-the-scenes snapshots and highlights, as well as more than 300 music documentaries, make up a rich archive on the National Centre for the Performing Arts website.

Beijing Forbidden City Concert Hall's "listening to Concerts Online" and Shanghai Concert Hall's "Cloud Concert Hall" have all launched new concert modes on platforms such as Weibo, wechat and official websites in new ways.

In the Netease cloud music, QQ music and other music media platforms, and epidemic-related activities and playlists are also real-time updates. Qq music as early as January 29 on the front page of the launch of "together tide over difficulties, refueling in Wuhan, " the special area, the entry of a new creation of anti-epidemic songs. Netease cloud music in a series of "Wuhan refueling, " the collection of songs, but also launched to combat the epidemic.

"there is no god in the world, only good people save you, the so-called mission is only to trust into responsibility... without the protection of angels, this city how to sleep. " January 25, the rapper "kindergarten killer" paid tribute to front-line workers by launching netease music's single "Guardian" , which also topped 40,000 reviews in a week.

To start with, Netease Cloud Music Online "fight against the epidemic, for the city should help" to collect special topics, original music contributions gradually increased, up to thousands of pieces, there are also songs by Han Hong, Tongyang, Li Ronghao, Angela Chang, Zheng Yunlong and others.

On the last day of the "house strawberry" live broadcast, the final performance was at the 2019 Guangzhou Strawberry Music Festival, where he sang in a song "on the field of hope" , "the bad weather will finally pass away. "
